{{Infobox Protected area | name = Desembarco del Granma National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = Gran Parque Nacional Desembarco del Granma.jpg | photo_caption = A waterfall in the national park | map = Cuba | map_caption = Location in Cuba | location = [[Cuba]] | nearest_city = [[Niquero]] | embedded1 = {{designation list | embed=yes | designation1 = WHS | designation1_date = 1999 <small>(23rd [[World Heritage Committee|session]])</small> | designation1_type = Natural | designation1_criteria = vii, viii | designation1_number = [http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/889 889] | designation1_free1name = State Party | designation1_free1value = Cuba | designation1_free2name = Region | designation1_free2value = [[List of World Heritage Sites in the Caribbean|Latin America and the Caribbean]] }} | coordinates = {{coords|19|53|00|N|77|38|00|W|display=inline, title}} | area = 261.80 km² | established = 1986 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }}
'''Desembarco del Granma National Park''' ({{lang-es|Parque Nacional Desembarco del Granma}}) is a [[national park]] in south-eastern [[Cuba]], in what is now [[Granma Province]]. The name of the park means "Landing of the Granma" and refers to the yacht in which [[Fidel Castro]], [[Che Guevara]], [[Raúl Castro]], and 79 of their supporters sailed from [[Mexico]] to Cuba in 1956 and incited the [[Cuban Revolution]].
It was listed by UNESCO as a World Heritage Site because of its [[Raised beach|uplifted marine terrace]]s and pristine sea cliffs.
==See also== *[[Niquero]], the municipality in which the national park is located. *''[[Granma (yacht)|Granma]]'', the revolutionaries' yacht that landed here.
